MatchingDonors AI Social Media Agent

An enterprise-grade, fully autonomous AI pipeline and web dashboard designed to drive organic social traffic for the MatchingDonors 501(c)(3) non-profit.

The system programmatically scrapes medical news, leverages Google Gemini to draft concise social media threads, and publishes them directly to social media platforms. It features a robust Human-in-the-Loop (HitL) architecture, allowing administrators to pause the autonomous engine, manually edit AI drafts in a "Draft Studio," and safely resume background operations without hitting API rate limits.

✨ Key Features
Autonomous Cron Engine: A background node-cron pipeline that handles the entire lifecycle: scraping, URL shortening, AI drafting, auto-condensing, publishing, and database logging.

Human-in-the-Loop "Draft Studio": A React-based interface allowing humans to take manual control of any crawler. It features a synchronized 30-second "Ghost Timer" that auto-publishes if no human edits are detected.

Traffic Analytics & Reporting: A built-in dashboard featuring interactive recharts visualizations to track inbound vs. outbound widget traffic, along with a 1-click .csv export tool for stakeholder reporting.

Smart Concurrency & Mutex Locks: Engineered with strict execution locks (isProcessing) to prevent overlapping cron schedules and race conditions during long-running API calls.

Multi-Source Scraping: Features an abstract CrawlerManager running 6 custom, anti-bot-resistant web scrapers targeting primary medical sources (OPTN, PLOS, PubMed, Daily Diabetes, etc.).

Pre-Publish Guardrails: Strict character-limit validation ensures all posts adhere to length limits, automatically utilizing AI to condense long text before failing over to human intervention.

🛠️ Tech Stack
Backend & AI Pipeline
Runtime: Node.js, TypeScript
Server: Express.js REST API
AI Provider: Google Gemini API (gemini-2.5-flash)
Database (Dual-Engine): PostgreSQL (Production/Swarm) & SQLite (Local fallback)
Automation: Node-Cron
Frontend Dashboard
Framework: React 18, Vite
Data Visualization: Recharts
Styling: Tailwind CSS v4
DevOps & Deployment
Containerization: Docker & Docker Compose
Orchestration: Kubernetes (K8s / Minikube)

🚀 Getting Started (Local Development)
1. Environment Variables. Create a .env file in the root directory of the project and add the following keys:
'
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_google_gemini_api_key
SOCIALMEDIA_IDENTIFIER=your_socialmedia_handle_or_email
SOCIALMEDIA_PASSWORD=your_socialmedia_app_password
PORT=3001
'

# Database Configuration (sqlite or postgres)
'
DB_TYPE=sqlite
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/matchingdonors_db
'

2. Standard Installation (Node.js)
# Install backend dependencies
'
npm install
'

# Install frontend dependencies
'
cd client
npm install
cd ..
'

# Terminal 1: Start the Node Backend
'
npx tsx src/server.ts
'

# Terminal 2: Start the React Frontend
'
cd client
npm run dev
'

🐳 Deployment (Docker & Kubernetes)
This application is fully containerized and production-ready.

Option A: Docker Compose (Single Node)
To spin up both the application and a local PostgreSQL database container simultaneously:
'
docker compose up --build
'

Option B: Kubernetes Swarm (Multi-Node Replica)
To deploy a highly available 5-node replica swarm connected to a centralized PostgreSQL service using Minikube:
'
# 1. Start your local cluster
minikube start --driver=docker

# 2. Build and load the image
docker build -t matchingdonors-agent:latest .
minikube image load matchingdonors-agent:latest

# 3. Deploy the K8s manifests
kubectl apply -f k8s/

# 4. Open the Dashboard UI
minikube service social-agent-service
'

⚙️ Architecture Workflow
Poll & Scrape: The CronService ticks every 60 seconds. It checks the Mutex lock, then uses the CrawlerManager to round-robin select a news source and scrape an un-published article.

Shorten & Delay: The article URL is shortened via TinyURL. The system engages a smart delay to protect against Gemini API rate limits.

AI Drafting: aiService prompts Gemini to generate an engaging, empathetic 2-part thread with appropriate hashtags.

Auto-Condense Loop: If any generated post exceeds 300 characters, the backend automatically prompts Gemini to condense it.

Human Override Window: The backend enters a 30-second delay. The React UI displays a yellow ⏳ Auto-publishing in 29s... warning.

If untouched: The system auto-publishes to the social media feed, records the URL in the database, and clears its cache.

If "Take Control" is clicked: The frontend sends a kill switch command to the backend. The backend pauses the Cron engine, hands off its cached AI drafts to the frontend Modal, and awaits manual human publication.

Public "Widget Mode" (Embeddable UI): The React frontend includes a stealth Widget Mode designed to be embedded securely on public-facing websites (like the MatchingDonors homepage) without exposing the administrative controls.

SEO Optimized: The widget displays clickable, highly descriptive article titles rather than raw URLs to boost page authority.

